-- Mainz Wins, Schalke Draws as German Soccer’s Bundesliga Resumes
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-08-11T17:50:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-11/mainz-wins-schalke-draws-as-german-soccer-s-bundesliga-resumes.html
 Mainz defeated Stuttgart and
Schalke drew with Hamburg today on the first weekend of
 Germany ’s Bundesliga season.  Mainz had a 3-2 home win, new signing Shinji Okazaki
scoring against his former team. Nicolai Mueller got the other
two goals.  Two days ago, European and German champion Bayern Munich
had a 3-1 win over Borussia Moenchengladbach in new coach Pep Guardiola’s first Bundesliga game.  Borussia Dortmund, runnerup to Bayern in both those
competitions, had a 4-0 victory at Augsburg yesterday. Off-season arrival Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang scored three times.  Among results in France this weekend, champion Paris Saint-Germain drew 1-1 at Montpellier, promoted Monaco won 2-0 at
Bordeaux and Lyon defeated Nice 4-0.  Ajax, seeking a fourth straight Dutch league title, lost 3-2 at AZ Alkmaar today, while Feyenoord slumped 4-1 at home to FC
Twente.  PSV Eindhoven  routed NEC Nijmegen 5-0 yesterday  The Italian and Spanish leagues have yet to resume.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 